article.headline: Binghamton 91, Vermont 83
article.story: BINGHAMTON, N.Y. -- D.J. Rivera had 29 points and 12 rebounds, and Malik Alvin added 19 points to lead Binghamton to a 91-83 overtime victory over on Thursday night. The Bearcats (10-4, 3-0 America East) have won six straight games. Maurice Joseph had 17 points for the Catamounts (9-5, 0-1), who had won six of eight. Nick Vier added 16 points for Vermont, while Mike Trimboli scored only eight points, 10 below his season average, missing all five 3-pointers he attempted. With the game tied at 75, Rivera missed free throw with 10 seconds left in regulation. He converted a three-point play to give Binghamton a one-point lead in overtime and Alvin followed with a 3 for an 81-77 lead with 3:50 left. Rivera scored five points and the Catamounts missed two layups and four 3-point attempts in the final 61 seconds.
